  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Set in the historic centre, The Duca d’Aosta has recently reopened after a complete 9 month restoration. With great care paid to quality and comfort, The Duca d’Aosta is one the city’s leading hotels – and it’s not hard to see why. The hotel has kept its original brick façade contrasting with elegant interiors featuring Italian style reminiscent of the mid-1900s. The bedrooms have been finished to an equally high standard with French oak floorboards and retro design. In the heart of the town, this hotel is the perfect base to explore this historic city as well as for getting the gondola for easy access to Pila’s slopes. The bus stops 20m from hotel or just 10 minutes’ walk (850m) to the Pila gondola. </span></p>]]></description>
